        "To create your character, follow these steps:\n\nStep 1: Create a Character Concept\nThink about the kind of character you want to play. In your case, you want a super dexterous and hearty cleric who uses a long bow.\n\nStep 2: Choose a Class\nSince you want to play a cleric, choose the cleric class. Clerics are divine spellcasters who are skilled in healing magic and have a wide range of support abilities.\n\nStep 3: Determine Ability Scores\nYour character's ability scores represent their physical and mental abilities. As a cleric, you'll want high Dexterity for your archery skills and high Constitution for your endurance. You can use one of the three methods described in the sidebar to determine your ability scores: Rolling, Point-Buy, or Standard Array.\n\nStep 4: Choose a Lineage\nLineage represents your character's hereditary traits. Choose a lineage that complements your concept of a dexterous and hearty cleric. Some lineages may provide bonuses to Dexterity or Constitution.\n\nStep 5: Choose a Heritage\nHeritage represents your character's upbringing and cultural background. Choose a heritage that fits your character concept and provides any additional bonuses or abilities.\n\nStep 6: Choose a Background\nBackgrounds represent what your character did before becoming an adventurer. Choose a background that aligns with your character's personality and provides skill proficiencies and other benefits.\n\nStep 7: Fill in the Blanks\nAt this point, most of your major decisions are made. Fill in the remaining details on your character sheet, such as name, appearance, and personality. You can also think about your character's history, but it's okay to develop those details as you play.\n\nOnce you've completed these steps, you'll have your character ready to embark on adventures as a dexterous and hearty cleric with a long bow!"
