        "CLASS FEATURES\nAs a cleric, you have the following class features.\n\nHIT POINTS\n- Hit Dice: 1d8 per cleric level\n- Hit Points at 1st Level: 8 + your CON modifier\n- Hit Points at Higher Levels: 1d8 (or 5) + your CON modifier per cleric level after 1st\n\nPROFICIENCIES\n- Armor: Light armor, medium armor, shields\n- Weapons: Simple weapons\n- Tools: None\n- Saves: WIS, CHA\n- Skills: Choose two from History, Insight, Medicine, Persuasion, and Religion\n\nSTARTING EQUIPMENT\nYou start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:\n- (a) a mace or (b) a warhammer (if proficient)\n- (a) scale mail, (b) leather armor, or (c) chain mail (if proficient)\n- (a) light crossbow and 20 bolts or (b) any simple weapon\n- (a) a priest's pack or (b) an explorer's pack\n- A shield and a holy symbol\n\nSPELLCASTING\n1st-Level Cleric Feature\n- Cantrips: Choose three cantrips from the divine circle spell list. You can learn more divine circle cantrips at higher levels.\n- Preparing and Casting Spells: Prepare spells from the divine circle spell list. The number of spells you can prepare is determined by your WIS modifier + your cleric level. You need to use a spell slot of the appropriate level to cast a prepared spell. You regain all used spell slots after a long rest.\n- Spellcasting Ability: Wisdom is your spellcasting ability. Your WIS modifier is used to determine the spell save DC and spell attack modifier.\n- Ritual Casting: You can cast ritual spells without needing to prepare them. You can learn ritual spells from rings you have spell slots for. Ritual spells do not count against the number of spells you learn at each level.\n\nSpellcasting Focus\n- You can use a holy symbol as a spellcasting focus for your spells.\n\nMANIFESTATION OF FAITH\n1st-Level Cleric Feature\n- Manifest Might: Gain proficiency with heavy armor and martial weapons. You can also infuse your weapon strikes with divine energy, dealing additional radiant or necrotic damage equal to your PB once per turn.\n- Manifest Miracles: Learn an additional cantrip from any circle of magic. You can add your PB to the damage you deal with any divine cantrip.\n\nCHANNEL DIVINITY\n2nd-Level Cleric Feature\n- You can channel divine energy from your deity to power effects beyond spells. You start with Turn the Profane as a Channel Divinity effect. Some domains grant additional effects as you level up.\n\nCLERIC SUBCLASS\n3rd-Level Cleric Feature\n- Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Life or War. Each domain grants domain spells and other features at 3rd level.\n\nIMPROVEMENT\n4th-Level Cleric Feature\n- Increase one ability score of your choice by 1 and choose a talent from the Magic Talent list that you meet the prerequisites for.\n\nDESTROY THE PROFANE\n5th-Level Cleric Feature\n- When a Fiend or Undead fails its save against your Turn the Profane feature, it is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is 1/2 or lower.\n\nCLERIC SUBCLASSES\n- Life Domain: Focuses on healing and vitality. Grants access to domain spells like bless and cure wounds. Channel Divinity: Preserve Life allows you to heal a number of hit points equal to five times your cleric level.\n- War Domain: Celebrates strength and victory. Grants access to domain spells like command and shield of faith. Channel Divinity: Mark of Triumph allows you to mark a creature, giving advantage on the first attack roll against it. The Disciple of War feature allows you to make an additional weapon attack after a successful hit a certain number of times per rest.\n\nNote: This is an edited and cleaned-up version of the original text."
